remarks: Transitive property of divisibility: if ` A ` divides ` B ` and ` B ` divides ` C ` , then ` A ` divides ` C ` .  Typically, ` C ` would be an integer, although the theorem holds for complex ` C ` .  (Contributed by NM, 3-May-2005.)
statement: nndivtr $p |- ( ( ( A e. NN /\ B e. NN /\ C e. CC ) /\ ( ( B / A ) e. NN /\ ( C / B ) e. NN ) ) -> ( C / A ) e. NN ) $.
